voicesplitting.utils

Class Beat

  • java.lang.Object
    • voicesplitting.utils.Beat
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Beat>

    public class Beat
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Beat>
    A Beat represents a single MIDI beat. It stores information about the onset time and tick number of the beat as well as what note occurs on it, and the beat number (in 32nd notes). Beats are Comparable and their natural ordering uses only beat, not any absolute timing information.
    Author:
    Andrew McLeod - 3 March, 2014
